  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 604b577af8a43c942bd5251f25245dcd, type: 3}
  m_Name: Spaceship_Lore
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GV.UI.ShipLoreData
  shipName: Spaceship
  tagline: Built by human hands. Fueled by split atoms. Aimed at the sky.
  rarity: Rare
  shipClass: Nuclear Strike Vessel
  originLabel: Alliance
  originName: Earth Countries in Akasya
  factionLabel: Pilots
  factionName: Atom Riders
  powerSystem: Nuclear-P Reactor Array
  combatRole: Rapid assault strike craft
  specialAbility: Reactor Overclock - temporarily boosts all weapons output beyond
    safe operating limits, trading hull integrity for devastating burst damage.
  backstory: "The Spaceship program began in Aurkana's NEO-TERRAn military labs
    as a classified weapons platform. The Earth Countries had watched the Kingdoms
    fly their ancient Vimanas for centuries, untouchable in the upper atmosphere.
    When QiNEXi engineers in Silkvale cracked Nuclear-P reactor miniaturization,
    everything changed. The first prototype was crude - a reinforced fuselage
    strapped to a Fission-class reactor with forward-mounted cannons. It exploded
    on its third test flight. But the design evolved. Aurkana funded it. Silkvale
    built it. Inkara's INTARi intelligence network stole Vimana flight data to
    refine the aerodynamics. Within five years, the Spaceship went from prototype
    to production. Nine Countries contributed technology: Aurkana's targeting
    systems, Silkvale's rapid-fire weapons, Inkara's sensor arrays, Elgorn Fall's
    Fusion reactor variants, Saharai's heat shielding. For the first time in
    history, humans from the surface could challenge the Kingdoms in their own sky.
    The Atom Riders are the pilots who fly these machines - engineers, deserters,
    mercenaries, and outcasts who bet their lives on human-built technology against
    divine weapons."
  strengths: "Nuclear-P reactors deliver raw firepower that matches or exceeds
    Astra-class weapons\nModular weapon hardpoints - pilots can customize loadouts
    between engagements\nAdvanced targeting computers compensate for pilot
    inexperience against Kingdom veterans\nField-repairable design; spare parts
    are manufactured, not excavated from ancient ruins"
  weaknesses: "Reactor instability under sustained combat - overheating causes
    cascading system failures\nNo Thara Resonance integration; entirely dependent
    on mechanical power with no spiritual energy backup\nRelatively fragile
    airframe compared to Vimana divine-alloy construction\nShort operational range
    - Nuclear-P fuel cells burn fast during high-output maneuvers"
  history: "Aurkana's NEO-TERRAn labs begin the classified Skybreaker program\n
    First prototype destroyed on third test flight; reactor containment failure\n
    Silkvale's QiNEXi engineers redesign the reactor housing for combat stress\n
    INTARi operatives steal Vimana aerodynamic data from Ratna Shila's archives\n
    Nine Countries pool technology into the unified Spaceship production line\n
    First combat deployment against Garudaja raiders near Garuda Vana's lower peaks\n
    Atom Riders formed as an independent pilot corps, outside any single Country's
    military command"
